headline: AT&T’s Valuation: Exploring Investment Potential After Major European Bond Raise
summary: AT&T just completed a major fixed-income offering in Europe, raising €2.25 billion through floating rate senior unsecured notes due in 2027. Moves like this are worth a closer look when weighing what to do with the stock. Not only does a fresh bond raise signal that lenders still have faith in AT&T’s balance sheet, it can also free up options for future investment, debt repayment, or shareholder returns. Each of these could have significant implications for current and prospective...
